The paper deals with the Max-Cut problem, which is a well-studied problem in computer science and optimization. The algorithm presented in the paper is based on spectral partitioning techniques, which are commonly used in graph theory and related fields. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The paper also involves analysis of the algorithm's approximation ratio, which suggests that it may be relevant to the sub-categories cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
